[[!comment format=mdwn
 username="joey"
 subject="""comment 1"""
 date="2026-03-02T15:28:01Z"
 content="""
The git-annex branch is automatically merged by git-annex,
it doesn't matter if it has unrelated histories or not. The merge will
always succeed, without conflicts.

All you need to do is pull the git-annex branch from a remote, and run
`git-annex merge`.

If for some reason you need to manually merge the git-annex branches,
yes all it takes is a simple union merge where on conflict you concatenate
both versions of the conflicted file together.
"""]]
